epitope mapping at the C-terminus of Stat3 of mouse origin
recommended for detection of Stat3 p92 of mouse, rat, human and Xenopus origin
The protein encoded by this gene is a member of the STAT protein family. In response to cytokines and
STAT family members are phosphorylated by the receptor associated kinases, and then form homo- or
translocate to the cell nucleus where they act as transcription activators. This protein is activated through
phosphorylation in response to various cytokines and growth factors including IFNs, EGF, IL5, IL6, HGF, LIF
This protein mediates the expression of a variety of genes in response to cell stimuli, and thus plays a key
many cellular processes such as cell growth and apoptosis.
COMMENT: We observe a single predominant band in all cell lines tested consistent with the size of
STAT3 (~88kD, indicated by arrow in left panel). While we observe multiple bands for all cell lines, we
see that only the expected band is immunoprecipitated specifically and efficiently (center panel,
indicated by arrow). Furthermore, we have identified STAT3 in multiple bands immunoprecipitated
from K562 cells (see validation assay #2). Therefore, sc-482 meets this ENCODE standard for validation.
Left. Western blot using antibody sc-482. Lanes contain nuclear lysates from (left to right) K562 cells, GM12878 cells, HeLa S3
cells, and HepG2 cells. Center. Immunoprecipitation of STAT3 from HeLaS3 cells using sc-482. Lane 1: input nuclear lysate, Lane
2: unbound material from immunoprecipitation with sc-482, Lane 3: material immunoprecipitated with sc-482, Lane 4: material
Right. Immunoprecipitation of STAT3 from K562 cells using sc-482. Lane 1: input nuclear
lysate, Lane 2: material immunoprecipitated using control IgG, Lane 3: material immunoprecipitated with sc-482. In all panels, arrow
indicates band consistent with expected size (88kD) of STAT3
Briefly, STAT3 was immunoprecipitated from K562 whole cell lysates using antibody sc-482. A
negative control IP using rabbit IgG was carried out in parallel and processed identically as follows.
The immunoprecipitated fraction was loaded on a 10% polyacrylamide gel (NuPAGE Bis-Tris Gel) and
separated with an Invitrogen NuPAGE electrophoresis system. The gel was silver-stained, gel
fragments corresponding to the bands indicated above in the Western blot image were excised and
destained using the Pierce SilverSNAP Stain for Mass Spectrometry kit. Proteins were then trypsinized
using the in-gel digestion method. Digested proteins were analyzed on an LTQ-Orbitrap (Thermo
Scientific) by the nanoLC-ESI-MS/MS technique. Peptides were identified by the SEQUEST algorithm
and filtered with a high confidence threshold (Protein false discovery rate < 1%, 2 peptides per
protein minimum). A schematic of the approximate location of the excised bands is shown in the
figure and all proteins identified in these bands are shown in the table along with the ratio of
peptides identified in the sc-482/Stat3 IP to peptides in the control IP. Stat3 is highlighted.
The primary immunoprecipitated band (indicated by arrow in the figure) was excised from the gel
and labeled band A. In this band, STAT3 was the most abundant protein (14 peptides) found to be
specifically immunoprecipitated by antibody sc-482. As can be seen in the Western blot submitted as
validation 1, we also observe minor bands that migrate with apparent molecular weights of ~100kD
and ~55kD. To identify these bands, we also excised regions of the gel corresponding to these sizes
(bands B and C respectively). As expected, Stat3 was identified at lower abundance in each of these
bands and it was present only in the IPs with antibody sc-482. Based on these results this antibody
meets the ENCODE standard for validation by this criterion.
